-- Telecom Argentina’s Quarterly Profit Rises 11% to $160 Million
-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 2012-05-04T14:48:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-04/telecom-argentina-s-quarterly-profit-rises-11-to-160-million.html
Telecom Argentina SA, the nation’s
largest telecommunications company, said first-quarter profit
increased 11 percent to 708 million pesos ($160 million) from a
year earlier, according to a filing on the securities
regulator’s website.  The company’s sales rose 24 percent to 5.1 billion pesos
from the same period last year, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in Buenos Aires at 
